body:
Earlier in League history, these two charts appeared to point at boring champion design: The [male](http://i.imgur.com/RtACReu.jpg) and [female](http://i.imgur.com/ZEhKvrm.jpg) body type charts.

I&#039;ve recently been noticing a similar trend with the way humanoid champions of each gender are presented. 

We already know that the male monster champions heavily outnumber the female monsters. So let&#039;s consider the humanoids only.

Male human (humanoid) champs (counting yordles because there are about as many female ones): {{champion:266}} {{champion:268}} {{champion:63}} {{champion:201}} {{champion:42}} {{champion:122}} {{champion:36}} {{champion:119}} {{champion:245}} {{champion:81}} {{champion:41}} {{champion:86}} {{champion:79}} {{champion:104}} {{champion:74}} {{champion:59}} {{champion:24}} {{champion:126}} {{champion:202}} {{champion:30}} {{champion:38}} {{champion:85}} {{champion:64}} {{champion:236}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:11}} {{champion:82}} {{champion:75}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:20}} {{champion:2}} {{champion:80}} {{champion:13}} {{champion:35}} {{champion:98}} {{champion:27}} {{champion:14}} {{champion:50}} {{champion:91}} {{champion:44}} {{champion:412}} {{champion:23}} {{champion:4}} {{champion:77}} {{champion:6}} {{champion:110}} {{champion:45}} {{champion:112}} {{champion:8}} {{champion:5}} {{champion:157}} {{champion:83}} {{champion:238}} {{champion:26}} {{champion:115}} 

Female humanoid champs: {{champion:103}} {{champion:84}} {{champion:1}} {{champion:22}} {{champion:51}} {{champion:69}} {{champion:131}} {{champion:60}} {{champion:28}} {{champion:114}} {{champion:420}} {{champion:39}} {{champion:40}} {{champion:222}} {{champion:429}} {{champion:55}} {{champion:10}} {{champion:203}} (Wolf is just a glorified particle effect imo){{champion:7}} {{champion:89}} {{champion:127}} {{champion:117}} {{champion:99}} {{champion:21}} {{champion:25}} {{champion:267}} {{champion:76}} {{champion:61}} {{champion:78}} {{champion:133}} {{champion:92}} {{champion:113}} {{champion:15}} {{champion:37}} {{champion:16}} {{champion:134}} {{champion:18}} {{champion:67}} {{champion:254}} {{champion:143}} 


Now, which of these are masked? 

Masked men: {{champion:268}}  (it&#039;s sort of his face, we&#039;re not certain?) {{champion:42}} {{champion:24}} {{champion:202}} {{champion:38}} {{champion:85}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:11}} {{champion:82}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:80}} {{champion:35}} {{champion:98}} {{champion:412}} {{champion:6}} {{champion:45}} {{champion:112}} {{champion:238}} {{champion:115}} 
Headgear or things obscuring most of their faces: {{champion:266}}{{champion:74}} {{champion:59}} {{champion:64}} {{champion:75}} {{champion:2}} {{champion:27}} {{champion:50}} {{champion:91}} {{champion:23}} {{champion:77}} {{champion:83}} {{champion:115}} 

Masked women:{{champion:84}} {{champion:203}} {{champion:10}} 

Covering headgear:{{champion:127}} {{champion:267}} {{champion:133}} {{champion:102}} 

Which of the masked men have skins that unmask them? {{champion:59}} {{champion:38}} {{champion:91}}  , two of those do not count completely.

Which of the masked women have skins which unmask them? {{champion:84}} {{champion:267}} {{champion:10}} {{champion:133}} {{champion:102}}.


If I were very much into social issues, I would say that this is because male champs are for self-insertion and female champs are for waifu.

But I&#039;m not. I&#039;m just really into Jhin and Azir and am dying for an unmasked Jhin and a pre-ascension Azir. ~~I wish Malz, Zed and Shen would drop the hijab too tbh.~~

EDIT: Feel free to correct me by the way, this all is off the top of my head.

